{
  "doc_id": "25515",
  "text": "Resistance to taxanes can be associated with the overexpression of P-gp [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , which has been confirmed in CRPC patients [CITATION_3] . Levels of P-gp expression are higher in docetaxel-resistant TaxR and DU145-DTXR cells as compared to that in docetaxel-sensitive, parental C4-2B and DU145 cells, respectively [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Similarly, P-gp is overexpressed in docetaxel-resistant DU145R and CWR22rv1R cells derived from the parental DU145 and CWR22rv1 cells, respectively [CITATION_6] . Consistent with these reports, we showed that P-gp was overexpressed in LNCaP95-DR cells, and that tariquidar treatment restored sensitivity to docetaxel. Therefore, overexpression of P-gp played a major role in the acquired resistance of LNCaP95 to docetaxel. Tariquidar is an anthranilic acid-derived third-generation P-gp inhibitor. Its efficacy has been evaluated in several clinical trials on different types of cancer including lung cancer, but there are no reports on its use for prostate cancer. Our study was the first report using tariquidar for prostate cancer cell lines.",
